{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|止|戈|t1=foot; to walk; to stop|t2=spear|ls=ic}} – army going on [[expedition]].

The graphical origin of {{lang|zh|武}} is described in the ''[[w:Spring and Autumn Annals|Spring and Autumn Annals]]'' {{defdate|481 BC}} as “to stop violence” ({{lang|zh|[[止]][[戈]][[為]][[武]]}}) – the ultimate state of warfare. This may be a misinterpretation as {{zh-l|*止}} is frequently used to mean “to walk” ({{zh-l|*趾}}), not “to stop”.
